	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="transcription">
				<pb facs="R 87-11 12 (11).jpg" n="2"/>
				<p><!--{{Ray Atherton}}, Arrest of [Professor Kantardjieff] in connection with <term ref="#t199" type="subject">anti-Semitic</term>
        <term ref="#t199" type="subject">demonstration </term>[sic], <placeName ref="#sofia">Sofia</placeName>, 4.4.1939, S. 2.</p>
      <p>Records of the Department of State relating to internal affairs of <placeName ref="#republic-of-bulgaria">Bulgaria</placeName>
        1910-1944, Washington 1982 (Mikrofilm-Edition): Dokument 874.4016/45--></p>
				<p>[...] There is no sympathy in <placeName ref="#republic-of-bulgaria">Bulgaria</placeName> for the <term ref="#t199" type="subject"
						>anti-Jewish demonstrations</term> of this organization ‚<orgName ref="#ehri_dr_workers_of_the_new_bulgaria">Workers of New
						Bulgaria</orgName>‘, especially as there is no <term ref="#t864" type="subject">Jewish</term> problem here, the total number
					of <term ref="#t864" type="subject">Jews</term> amounting to less than 55,000. The <term ref="#t864" type="subject">Jews</term>
					are not active in <term ref="#t983" type="subject">political</term> and public life; there are none among the <term ref="#t1077"
						type="subject">army</term> officers and almost none in civil service. Their sphere of activity is <term ref="#t924"
						type="subject">business</term>, <term ref="#t937" type="subject">industry</term> and small <term ref="#t933" type="subject"
						>trades</term>, and there are very few <term ref="#t864" type="subject">Jews</term> in the liberal professions and <term
						ref="#t673" type="subject">arts</term>. The anti-Jewish <term ref="#t986" type="subject">propaganda</term> conducted by the
						‚<orgName ref="#ehri_dr_workers_of_the_new_bulgaria">Workers of New Bulgaria</orgName>‘ is of foreign origin and is, it is
					believed, directly encouraged from <placeName ref="#federal-republic-of-germany">Germany</placeName>.[...]</p>
			</div>
